    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i mean \"negligible\" is still a huge assumption though, right? if we're talking about the scale of global mining and the huge amounts of concrete and steel needed for a complete grid overhaul, the damage is pretty significant. it feels like you're just dismissing the huge ecological footprint of renewables to make the math work for one side. can't you just list the trade-offs for both without declaring a \"winner\"?",
